OL,3,CRadio 4 LW/MW, linear BBC services and
OL,4,Cfuture BBC funding
OL,6,FSome low power Radio 4 medium wave
OL,7,Ftransmitters, which were principally
OL,8,Fdesigned to aid reception in areas
OL,9,Fwhere the LW reception was not so
OL,10,Frobust, will indeed close next month.
OL,12,FBut Radio 4 LW transmission isn't
OL,13,Fquite dead yet.
OL,15,FIt will stay on the air for the moment
OL,16,Fand efforts will continue to migrate
OL,17,Fthe last LW listeners to FM or digital
OL,18,Fplatforms before the signal finally
OL,19,Fgoes.
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G2/12
