OL,3,CRadio 4 LW/MW, linear BBC services and
OL,4,Cfuture BBC funding
OL,6,FIf anything, you could accuse the BBC
OL,7,Fof undue overcaution when it comes to
OL,8,Fclosing Radio 4 LW.
OL,10,FIt's now two years since the
OL,11,Fannouncement that separate LW
OL,12,Fprogrammes were to end. This has been
OL,13,Factively promoted on air for a year.
OL,15,FThe decision to keep the transmitter
OL,16,Fitself alive for longer ` linked to
OL,17,Fproviding switching signals for some
OL,18,Felectricity meters ` did not
OL,19,Fautomatically imply keeping Radio 4 LW
OL,20,Fon air. A retuning loop, for instance,
OL,21,Fcould have been broadcast instead.
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G3/12
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
