OL,3,CRadio 4 LW/MW, linear BBC services and
OL,4,Cfuture BBC funding
OL,6,FBut clearly continuing with the
OL,7,Fservice for a little longer is
OL,8,Fconsidered viable and worthwhile `
OL,9,Fthough just how many benefit in
OL,10,Fpractice is not public knowledge. It's
OL,11,Fprobably very low.
OL,13,FThe transfer of the Daily Service and
OL,14,FYesterday in Parliament to Radio 4
OL,15,FExtra appears to cast doubt over
OL,16,Fwhether proposals announced two years
OL,17,Fago to turn Radio 4 Extra into an on-
OL,18,Fdemand, online service will still go
OL,19,Fahead. It sounds safe as a linear
OL,20,Fservice for the foreseeable future too.
