OL,3,CRadio 4 LW/MW, linear BBC services and
OL,4,Cfuture BBC funding
OL,6,FAnyone without a digital radio or
OL,7,Fsmart speaker will be advised they can
OL,8,Flisten to the Daily Service or
OL,9,FYesterday in Parliament via Radio 4
OL,10,FExtra on Freeview.
OL,12,FThose who confidently predict the end
OL,13,Fof Freeview and linear BBC services in
OL,14,Fthe medium term would be wise to
OL,15,Fconsider all this.
OL,17,FIt will be interesting to see how
OL,18,FFreely ` the internet equivalent of
OL,19,FFreeview ` develops.
OL,21,FTo succeed it will need to offer
OL,22,Fconsumers a strong proposition.
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G5/12
